    CS2 Bhop Script operates through a sophisticated input simulation system that monitors player movement and jump timing. The script detects when the player is in the air and automatically executes the next jump at the exact millisecond of landing, achieving perfect bunny hops consistently. It uses low-level keyboard hooks for minimal latency and includes customizable timing adjustments to account for different tick rates and personal preferences. The script can be toggled on/off with a configurable hotkey and runs invisibly in the background .
    
